<div id="review_4500736260" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4500736260" />
    <a title="Richard Thompson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11657479-richard-thompson"><img alt="Richard Thompson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1530711053p2/11657479.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4500736260?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Richard Thompson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Richard Thompson" href="/user/show/11657479-richard-thompson">Richard Thompson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/36655622-the-non-existent-knight">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/11657479-richard-thompson?shelf=italian-literature">italian-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4500736260" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer150127266924857683">Now I have finished the cycle of three novellas that also includes The Cloven Viscount and The Baron In The Trees. They are all great fun and can be enjoyed by casual readers who may find Mr. Calvino&apos;s more intellectual novels daunting. In this one Mr. Calvino mocks tales of chivalry much as Cervantes does in Don Quixote, giving us a variety of characters who bumble through life in moronic obedience to concepts of knightly honor. The title character is a suit of armor with no one inside, a class</span>
  <span id="freeText150127266924857683" style="display:none">Now I have finished the cycle of three novellas that also includes The Cloven Viscount and The Baron In The Trees. They are all great fun and can be enjoyed by casual readers who may find Mr. Calvino's more intellectual novels daunting. In this one Mr. Calvino mocks tales of chivalry much as Cervantes does in Don Quixote, giving us a variety of characters who bumble through life in moronic obedience to concepts of knightly honor. The title character is a suit of armor with no one inside, a classic empty suit. He is in most respects a perfect knight, but in this world a perfect knight is a perfect fool. It made me think of the Edith Wharton character from old New York society whose one distinguishing feature was that he looked great in a tuxedo. </span>
  <a data-text-id="150127266924857683" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


