<div id="review_2646385784" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2646385784" />
    <a title="Kent Winward" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1054712-kent-winward"><img alt="Kent Winward" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1408199296p2/1054712.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2646385784?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kent Winward" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kent Winward" href="/user/show/1054712-kent-winward">Kent Winward</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/19637099-the-nonexistent-knight">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2646385784" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11434832244060508336">When combined with <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20892444.The_Cloven_Viscount' title='The Cloven Viscount by Italo Calvino' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Cloven Viscount</a>and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9804.The_Baron_in_the_Trees' title='The Baron in the Trees by Italo Calvino' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Baron in the Trees</a>, Calvino is doing the work of the myth maker, resurrecting the art of the fairy tale, and fully exploring the vagaries and inconsistencies of the human condition. <br/><br/>On this New Year&apos;s Day, I&apos;m reflecting on these books and it is as unsettling as it is life affirming. </span>
  <span id="freeText11434832244060508336" style="display:none">When combined with <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20892444.The_Cloven_Viscount" title="The Cloven Viscount by Italo Calvino" rel="nofollow noopener">The Cloven Viscount</a>and <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9804.The_Baron_in_the_Trees" title="The Baron in the Trees by Italo Calvino" rel="nofollow noopener">The Baron in the Trees</a>, Calvino is doing the work of the myth maker, resurrecting the art of the fairy tale, and fully exploring the vagaries and inconsistencies of the human condition. <br /><br />On this New Year's Day, I'm reflecting on these books and it is as unsettling as it is life affirming. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11434832244060508336" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

