<div id="review_2765097002" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2765097002" />
    <a title="Dinu Maria" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/89318848-dinu-maria"><img alt="Dinu Maria" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1639655400p2/89318848.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2765097002?book_show_action=true">Mar 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dinu Maria" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dinu Maria" href="/user/show/89318848-dinu-maria">Dinu Maria</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2765097002" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14111076876047158477">Growing up, at school we had to learn all Italian authors, and one that I could not stand was Italo Calvino. I still don’t know why, perhaps because I didn’t like to read at that time, but I found Calvino incredibly boring and hard to understand. In high school we started talking about Calvino, his life and works and the first book we had to read was “Il cavaliere Inesistente”. <br/>I have never loved a book this much, it attracted me instantly and I immediately started regretting not reading it when</span>
  <span id="freeText14111076876047158477" style="display:none">Growing up, at school we had to learn all Italian authors, and one that I could not stand was Italo Calvino. I still don’t know why, perhaps because I didn’t like to read at that time, but I found Calvino incredibly boring and hard to understand. In high school we started talking about Calvino, his life and works and the first book we had to read was “Il cavaliere Inesistente”. <br />I have never loved a book this much, it attracted me instantly and I immediately started regretting not reading it when I first had the chance. And now I think I needed to grow a little older in order to like and understand his writing and the plot. An amazing book that certainly did not disappoint me. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14111076876047158477" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


